# 06.07 Release Process

## Overview

The Release Process defines how cmdOS software versions are prepared, validated, published, and maintained.

Because cmdOS is an AI Execution Operating System consisting of multiple interconnected components, releases must follow a controlled process to ensure:

- System stability
- Compatibility
- Security
- Performance
- User reliability

Core principle:

Development

↓

Validation

↓

Release Preparation

↓

Deployment

↓

Monitoring

↓

Improvement

---

# 1. Release Process Purpose

The purpose of the Release Process is to establish a consistent method for delivering cmdOS updates.

It enables:

- Predictable releases
- Safer deployments
- Better version management
- Easier maintenance
- Continuous product improvement

---

# 2. Release Architecture Position

The Release Process connects development activities with production delivery.

Architecture relationship:

Developer

↓

