# 3. Release Philosophy

cmdOS follows a controlled and iterative release philosophy.

Every release should:

- Improve system capability
- Maintain compatibility
- Protect user data
- Preserve system stability

Release principle:

Small Improvements

↓

Continuous Delivery

↓

Long-Term Evolution

---

# 4. Release Types

cmdOS supports multiple release categories.

---

# Development Release

## Purpose

Used for internal development and experimentation.

Characteristics:

- Frequent updates
- Experimental features
- Limited availability

Users:

- Core developers
- Internal testers

---

# Alpha Release

## Purpose

Early public testing phase.

Characteristics:

- New features
- Active development
- Possible instability

Users:

- Early adopters
- Developers

---

# Beta Release

## Purpose

Feature validation before production.

Characteristics:

- More stable
- Larger testing group
- Performance optimization

Users:

- Community testers
- Partners

---

# Stable Release

## Purpose

Production-ready version.

Characteristics:

- Fully tested
- Reliable
- Supported officially

Users:

- All customers

